<article>
  <p>Hey Flourishites 👋</p>
  <p>Multiple currencies is live! 💰</p>
  <p>This means that all members will be able to participate using all <a href="https://developer.paypal.com/docs/reports/reference/paypal-supported-currencies/">Paypal supported currencies</a>....except Taiwanese dollars*. 😅</p> 
  <p><strong>You can now go to the membership section and change your currency.</strong></p>
  <p>What ever your currency is set to at the time of the weekly distribution that is what your dividend will be paid out in.<p>
  <p>Contributions can also be sent in the same set of supported currencies.</p>
  <p>For those keen to try, let me know how it goes. 🙏</p>
  <p>-Luke-</p>
  <p>* I realised as I was almost finished that the service I'm using to update the rates each day, EU Central Bank, does not include TWD.</p>
</article>
<article>
  <p><b>Distribution <%= @next_distribution.name %> Preview</b></p>
  <ul>
    <li><b>Date:</b> <%= @next_distribution.date_formatted %></li>
    <li><b>Total Contributions:</b> <%= @next_distribution.total_pool_formatted(@member.currency) %></li>
    <li><b>Members:</b> <%= @next_distribution.member_count %></li>
    <li><b>Dividend:</b> <%= @next_distribution.dividend_amount_formatted(@member.currency) %></li>
  </ul>
  <a><%= link_to "View Past Distributions", distributions_url %></a>
</article>
<article>
<p><b>Recent Contributions</p></b>
  <% if @recent_contributions.none? %>
    <p>[No contributions in the last week]</p>
  <% else %>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Date</th>
          <th>Amount</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <% @recent_contributions.each do |contribution| %>
          <tr>
            <td><%= contribution.created_at_formatted %></td>
            <td><%= contribution.amount_formatted %></td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  <% end %>
</article>
<article>
  <p><b>Weekly Expenses</p></b>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Item</th>
        <th>Amount</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <% @expenses.each do |expense| %>
        <tr>
          <td><%= expense.name %></td>
          <td><%= expense.amount_formatted %></td>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
      <tr>
        <td><b>Total Deducted from Pool</b></td>
        <td><b><%= @total_expenses_formatted %></b></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</article>
